Most people just read Piketty to page 26 anyway. So anyone claiming they read it, probably not.<p>The Summer&#x27;s Most Unread Book Is…
<a href="http://www.wsj.com/articles/the-summers-most-unread-book-is-1404417569" rel="nofollow">http://www.wsj.com/articles/the-summers-most-unread-book-is-...</a><p>&quot;&quot;Capital in the Twenty-First Century&quot; by Thomas Piketty: 2.4% 
Yes, it came out just three months ago. But the contest isn&#x27;t even close. Mr. Piketty&#x27;s book is almost 700 pages long, and the last of the top five popular highlights appears on page 26. Stephen Hawking is off the hook; from now on, this measure should be known as the Piketty Index.&quot;
